cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a novel approach for EEG-based driver drowsiness estimation using machine learning techniques. The approach involves feature weighting and episodic training, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
